OL,3,CWidow calls for law change after
OL,4,Chusband's brain tumour death
OL,6,FMrs James is heading a campaign
OL,7,Fcalling for patients to have the right
OL,8,Fto have their tissue frozen and stored
OL,9,Fafter surgery, enabling access to
OL,10,Fpersonalised treatments and genetic
OL,11,Ftests.
OL,13,FThe 36-year-old, from Caerphilly, said
OL,14,Fthis is done "inconsistently" across
OL,15,Fthe NHS, creating a postcode lottery
OL,16,Fof care.
OL,18,FShe is calling for a change in the
OL,19,Flaw, dubbed Owain's Law, which would
OL,20,Flet patients give consent about what
OL,21,Fhappens to their tissue.
