OL,3,CWidow calls for law change after
OL,4,Chusband's brain tumour death
OL,6,FMrs James said she believes her
OL,7,Fhusband would still be alive had the
OL,8,Flaw been in place when he was
OL,9,Freceiving treatment.
OL,11,FThe issue is to be discussed in a
OL,12,FWestminster Hall debate on Wednesday.
OL,14,FMr James, a father of one, was
OL,15,Fdiagnosed with brain cancer in
OL,16,FSeptember 2022. He had a 14cm tumour,
OL,17,Fhalf of which medics were able to
OL,18,Fsafely remove during surgery.
