OL,3,CWidow calls for law change after
OL,4,Chusband's brain tumour death
OL,6,F"And I feel like that choice for us
OL,7,Fwas taken out of our hands by a
OL,8,Fdecision made by a pathologist who had
OL,9,Fno idea what we were going to do and
OL,10,Fdidn't think it right to get the
OL,11,Frelevant consent on what they should
OL,12,Fdo with his tissue."
OL,14,FShe added: "I think patients should
OL,15,Fhave control and informed consent over
OL,16,Fwhat happens to their tissue and how
OL,17,Fit's stored and whether they want to
OL,18,Fuse it for future treatments or
OL,19,Fresearch or through the testing,
OL,20,Fwhatever that might be.
